Path: godot/tutorials/physics/interpolation/advanced_physics_interpolation.rst
Summary: This section explains how MultiMeshes can be used for physics interpolation on a per-instance basis.
MultiMeshes can control several instances from the same Node. Therefore, they have some extra functions for controlling interpolation functionality on a per-instance basis. You should explore these functions if you are using interpolated MultiMeshes.

Key methods for interpolated MultiMeshes:
- MultiMesh.reset_instance_physics_interpolation
- MultiMesh.set_buffer_interpolated

Full details are in the MultiMesh documentation.